cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.RO 

This paper is about reinforcement learning algorithms and their regret bounds in the infinite-horizon discounted Markov decision process (MDP) setting. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and their performance, which could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with decision-making processes, which could be classified under multi-agent systems (cs.MA) or robotics (cs.RO).
